rComments: Dena is an amazing professor who is an even more amazing person. I recommend taking any class you can with her because they're rarely difficult and because of that lack of pressure you learn more, in my opinion. Lovely lady and I could not recommend  her more!

Dena is the type of teacher who is more of a friend than a teacher. She encourages all of her students to be involved in discussion, and really makes it a comfortable learning environment. Anyone who has the privilege of knowing her is a really, really lucky person.

As long as you go to her class and participate, you'll get an A. She's very understanding and an awesome teacher to have. I had her for Crown Core 80B and got 2B's and 2A's on her paper and passed her class with an A. She gives really good feedback on papers. I never had to go to her office hours.

Dena is truly an inspiration. She's one of the only teachers who actually cares for her students and makes them feel as if they are truly important and significant. Won't lie, she grades a little tough on the essays, but she grades fairly. She is willing to help you w/ anything, so go to office hours. Would take any class she taught!

Hands down my favorite professor ever. Dena is caring and interesting and everything you want in a professor. This was an 8 am and she was very forgiving about tardies and absences (as long as there wasn't anything important like an in-class debate) and she even brought in a blanket for me because I'd be cold in the morning. 100/10 I LOVE YOU DENA!

Dena is an excellent professor! I would definitely recommend taking her class. Her lectures are lively and interesting and keep the whole class participating. There is a paper due every other week, but the prompts are very clear and the papers aren't hard. If you do happen to get a C, or even a B on a paper, go to Dena's office hours and revise it.
She is amazing! You really can't ask for a better professor than Dena. Just do the readings and participate in class.

DENA IS AMAZING! She's hilarious and is by far one of the nicest professors at UCSC. Participation is worth a lot in her class, but as long as you talk and put in effort on your essays (take advantage of the revision option!), you will pass the class.

Dena is the best professor I have ever had at UCSC. Not only is she super caring for all of her students, but she's also an incredible person. She genuinely cares about everything that students share, and the class is never boring. She has a great sense of humor, and does a good job engaging people in discussions, even if you are quiet.

Dena is one of the best professors at UCSC. She genuinely cares for her students and you will spend most lectures going around in a circle talking about the readings and relating them to your life. She makes the (not so interesting) material seem interesting and she knows how to engage her students. TAKE HER CLASS!! :)

I absolutely love Dena! For only having her for a quarter, I already feel like she's one of the best teachers I've had. She's super warm and caring and quite an interesting lady with many fun stories to share. Her writing advice helped so much and she cares a lot about her students. She's also really funny which is always great.
Dena is such an amazing professor. If you have the chance to take her class, do it. She is so sweet and really takes the time to get to know her students.

Dena is very helpful. Most days we have lengthy class discussions on reading material. Make sure you work hard on any written assignments; she will see effort if you actually give it and grade accordingly. As long as you try, you will definitely pass the class.

Dena is the greatest professor you will meet at UCSC. She is so helpful and caring, and that helps the class environment overall. She is one incredible professor; very, extremely knowledgeable of the curriculum she teaches and always willing to help you improve. I could not have asked for a better instructor. She is amazing!

She is awesome! She is so chill and has always the most entertaining conversations! She is definitely a professor you can go to for anything! I feel as if she knows me more as a person than as a student. She's just great!
Dena is so friendly and makes the class feel so comfortable. I loved the core class so much, she is a lovable great teacher. ^_^ Great first core class of my Freshman year.
BEST CLASS EVER!!!

Probably the greatest teacher to step on the UCSC campus. She doesn't even teach for any salary. She made core my favorite class to go to even though all of my other friends were complaining how horrible their core classes were. That just reveals how gangsta and amazing she is.

Extremely kind woman, very helpful in teaching writing. Offers her kindness in and outside the classroom. Offers to edit essays for outside classes, and even letters to get you out of write ups. Not afraid to open up to the class about her personal experiences and is overall a very warm person.

People on my floor constantly complained about Core, but my class with Dena was great! She was really helpful and loved keeping conversations with the class. The students were very free to talk about any topic and Dena made sure to make us all comfortable with each other. This was a very easy, interesting, and fun class.
Dena is the best! Her class is always interesting because she lets to the students choose discussion topics. She is understanding, thoughtful, and lets you revise all your essays for a better grade.
Had her for freshman core. Awesome professor! Always made class interesting.

Dena is an extremely nice teacher who is always willing to review your essays one on one with you during her office hours. She takes an open forum approach in her classroom by letting the students lead discussions every Friday to get them engaged in intellectual topics.  Overall, Dena is very approachable and nice.

I had Dena for my freshman core, and she was amazing! Incredibly nice, enthusiastic. She had a lot interest and respect for students, which is different from most professors you meet. She was really easygoing. I would recommend her, but I'm not sure if she's teaching anymore. I think she may teach only one or two classes per quarter.
amazing teacher, extremely understanding. interested in the students and their learning progress.I became a better student because of her class. great teacher I highly recommend her!
Dena is a very fun teacher.  She is entertaining and interesting and always willing to help.  Take this class if you want to learn about public speaking and mock trial.  Easy A.

Dena is a fantastic teacher. Incredibly witty, she uses real-life scenarios and anecdotes to help us learn. She is sharp, modern, and clear in her explanations and lessons. She only taught us for a few classes because our instructor had to step back due to illness, but everyone in the class wished that we could have had her for the entire year.
Dena is so cool. She is relatable, hilarious, and really helps students think for themselves. Very enthusiastic and positive.

This is my favorite professor! She is awesome! She keeps the class engaged, her stories are both academic and personal. You will never be bored in this class. We always have great debates in our class. She is also very concerned with improving the class, by using her students opinions.

Amazing teacher. Even though we constantly go off on small tangents in class I still feel like I understand everything by the time we are finished. She is helping me get through Core and she makes it so fun.

Amazing teacher.  She got us engaged in the material, and inspired constant participation.  While we read every book except Beccaria, cover to cover, we branched out during class to compare our experiences in relation to what we read.  She was happy to be there, happy to teach, and never made any student feel bad for asking questions.  Great Lady.

Amazing teacher. She got us engaged in the material and inspired constant student participation.  While we read all the books but Beccaria cover to cover, we branched out during the class to relate our personal experiences to what we read.  She was always willing to talk after class and she never thought less of students asking "dumb" questions.
